<UserControl x:Class="TestDataContextBindings.Views.UserControls.PageInfo"
             xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" 
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008" 
             xmlns:local="clr-namespace:TestDataContextBindings.Views.UserControls"
             xmlns:v="clr-namespace:TestDataContextBindings.Views"
             mc:Ignorable="d" 
             d:DesignHeight="450" d:DesignWidth="800">
    
    <Grid HorizontalAlignment="Center" VerticalAlignment="Center" >
        <TextBlock>
            <Bold><Span Foreground="Blue" TextDecorations="Underline">How it works:</Span></Bold>
            <LineBreak/> <Span FontStyle="Italic">
            When a Button is clicked, the MainViewModel will pass the selected ViewModel to the ContentPresenter control,
            <LineBreak/>the ContentPresenter control will them look for a template and loads it dislaying 
            <LineBreak/>the associated UserControl and the ViewModel is automatically set 
            <LineBreak/>to the UserControl DataContext property and DataBinding is applied.
            </Span>
        </TextBlock>
    </Grid>
</UserControl>
